======================================================================
                     JUDGEMENT OF CFJ 867

    Rule 1597 should be interpreted such that, whenever a Rule
    directly requires a transfer of Currencies to take place,
    and when the transfer would result in the Treasury being
    transferred from containing a negative quantity of the
    Currency transferred, the transfer does not take place,
    unless the Rule requiring the transfer takes precedence over
    Rule 1597.

